After suffering through this for years and just now finding a fix, I thought I'd leave this here for others who get the annoying registration pop-up each time they launch Photoshop (as I understand it this only happens in Vista and 7 and occurs with legal versions of CS2 as well).

1. Right-click Adobe Photoshop CS2 > Run as Administrator.

2. After it launches, close the pop-up by clicking "do not register" as you normally would, then close Photoshop.

3. Now launch Photoshop normally. Voila! You should no longer get the pop-up.
